        "source": "// Broken example — what happens if you forget PhantomData.\n//\n// A struct with a type parameter that isn't used by any field is\n// rejected with E0392: \"parameter `Unit` is never used\". The compiler\n// insists that every type parameter either be stored or be declared\n// as phantom.\n//\n// This file is expected to FAIL to compile.\n\n// Mistake #1: generic parameter `Unit` not referenced anywhere.\npub struct Duration<Unit> {\n    amount: u64,\n}\n// ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^ error[E0392]: parameter `Unit` is never used\n//                        consider removing `Unit`, referring to it in a\n//                        field, or using a marker such as `PhantomData`\n\n// Mistake #2: pass a Duration<Seconds> where Duration<Milliseconds>\n// is expected. Without PhantomData, the above doesn't even compile;\n// with PhantomData (see code/idiomatic.rs), this is the downstream\n// error you'd see.\npub struct Seconds;\npub struct Milliseconds;\n\npub fn sleep_for_ms(_d: Duration<Milliseconds>) { /* ... */ }\n\nfn main() {\n    // If we fixed #1, this call would still be wrong:\n    //   sleep_for_ms(Duration::<Seconds> { amount: 5 });\n    //   ^^^^^^^^^^^^ error[E0308]: mismatched types\n    //                expected `Duration<Milliseconds>`,\n    //                found `Duration<Seconds>`\n}\n",
        "playground": "https://play.rust-lang.org/?version=stable&mode=debug&edition=2021&code=%2F%2F%20Broken%20example%20%E2%80%94%20what%20happens%20if%20you%20forget%20PhantomData.%0A%2F%2F%0A%2F%2F%20A%20struct%20with%20a%20type%20parameter%20that%20isn't%20used%20by%20any%20field%20is%0A%2F%2F%20rejected%20with%20E0392%3A%20%22parameter%20%60Unit%60%20is%20never%20used%22.%20The%20compiler%0A%2F%2F%20insists%20that%20every%20type%20parameter%20either%20be%20stored%20or%20be%20declared%0A%2F%2F%20as%20phantom.%0A%2F%2F%0A%2F%2F%20This%20file%20is%20expected%20to%20FAIL%20to%20compile.%0A%0A%2F%2F%20Mistake%20%231%3A%20generic%20parameter%20%60Unit%60%20not%20referenced%20anywhere.%0Apub%20struct%20Duration%3CUnit%3E%20%7B%0A%20%20%20%20amount%3A%20u64%2C%0A%7D%0A%2F%2F%20%5E%5E%5E%5E%5E%5E%5E%5E%5E%5E%5E%5E%5E%5E%5E%5E%5E%5E%5E%5E%5E%5E%20error%5BE0392%5D%3A%20parameter%20%60Unit%60%20is%20never%20used%0A%2F%2F%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20consider%20removing%20%60Unit%60%2C%20referring%20to%20it%20in%20a%0A%2F%2F%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20field%2C%20or%20using%20a%20marker%20such%20as%20%60PhantomData%60%0A%0A%2F%2F%20Mistake%20%232%3A%20pass%20a%20Duration%3CSeconds%3E%20where%20Duration%3CMilliseconds%3E%0A%2F%2F%20is%20expected.%20Without%20PhantomData%2C%20the%20above%20doesn't%20even%20compile%3B%0A%2F%2F%20with%20PhantomData%20(see%20code%2Fidiomatic.rs)%2C%20this%20is%20the%20downstream%0A%2F%2F%20error%20you'd%20see.%0Apub%20struct%20Seconds%3B%0Apub%20struct%20Milliseconds%3B%0A%0Apub%20fn%20sleep_for_ms(_d%3A%20Duration%3CMilliseconds%3E)%20%7B%20%2F*%20...%20*%2F%20%7D%0A%0Afn%20main()%20%7B%0A%20%20%20%20%2F%2F%20If%20we%20fixed%20%231%2C%20this%20call%20would%20still%20be%20wrong%3A%0A%20%20%20%20%2F%2F%20%20%20sleep_for_ms(Duration%3A%3A%3CSeconds%3E%20%7B%20amount%3A%205%20%7D)%3B%0A%20%20%20%20%2F%2F%20%20%20%5E%5E%5E%5E%5E%5E%5E%5E%5E%5E%5E%5E%20error%5BE0308%5D%3A%20mismatched%20types%0A%20%20%20%20%2F%2F%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20expected%20%60Duration%3CMilliseconds%3E%60%2C%0A%20%20%20%20%2F%2F%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20found%20%60Duration%3CSeconds%3E%60%0A%7D%0A"
